p: Analysis of the partial G gene sequence showed that 41% (48/117) of RSV-A were genotype NA1 ( Fig. 2). This genotype was predominant in 2012, but was relatively absent thereafter. An additional 58.1% (68/117) of RSV-A were ON1, which co-circulated with NA1 in 2012 and remained the only RSV-A genotype detected from 2013 onward. Only one sample was NA3, which appeared in 2012. For RSV-B, most were BA9 (92.6%, 87/94) ( Fig. 3). The remainders were BA10 (4.3%, 4/94) and BA-C (3.2%, 3/94), which only appeared in 2012 and 2015. One sample (TH-CU448) was co-infected with RSV-A genotype ON1 and RSV-B genotype BA9.
